entry.ptxt: Transmission Range Sensor Circuit Malfunction (PRNDL Input)
Transmission Fluid Temperature Sensor “A” Circuit Range / Performance
Transmission fluid temperature sensor variation is less than specified value even though engine was running for specified time after engine start.
Transmission Fluid Temperature Sensor “A” Circuit Low
Sensor output voltage is too low.
Transmission Fluid Temperature Sensor “A” Circuit High
Sensor output voltage is too high.
Input / Turbine Speed Sensor “A” Circuit No Signal
No sensor signal is detected although output speed sensor signal is inputted.
Output Speed Sensor Circuit No Signal
No sensor signal is inputted although input speed sensor signal is inputted.
Torque Converter Clutch Circuit Performance or Stuck Off
Difference in revolution between engine and input shaft is too large although TCM is commanding TCC pressure control solenoid to turn ON.
Torque Converter Clutch Circuit Stuck On
Difference in revolution between engine and input shaft is too small although TCM is commanding TCC pressure control solenoid to turn OFF.
Shift Solenoid “A” Performance or Stuck Off
The gear commanded by TCM does not match the actual gear when driving.
The gear commanded by TCM does not match the actual gear when driving.
Shift Solenoid “B” Performance or Stuck Off
The gear commanded by TCM does not match the actual gear when driving.
The gear commanded by TCM does not match the actual gear when driving.
Shift Solenoid “E” Performance or Stuck Off
The gear commanded by TCM does not match the actual gear when driving.

The gear commanded by TCM does not match the actual gear when driving.
Pressure Control Solenoid “A” Control Circuit Range / Performance
Difference between target current of control solenoid circuit and monitor current of control solenoid circuit is more than specified.
Pressure Control Solenoid “A” Control Circuit Low
No electric flow is detected on pressure control solenoid circuit.
Pressure Control Solenoid “A” Control Circuit High
Too much electric flow is detected on pressure control solenoid circuit.
Pressure Control Solenoid “B” Control Circuit Range / Performance
Difference between target current of control solenoid circuit and monitor current of control solenoid circuit is more than specified.
Pressure Control Solenoid “B” Control Circuit Low
No electric flow is detected on pressure control solenoid circuit.
Pressure Control Solenoid “B” Control Circuit High

Pressure Control Solenoid “C” Control Circuit Range / Performance
Difference between target current of control solenoid circuit and monitor current of control solenoid circuit is more than specified.
Pressure Control Solenoid “C” Control Circuit Low
No electric flow is detected on pressure control solenoid circuit.
Pressure Control Solenoid “C” Control Circuit High
Too much electric flow is detected on pressure control solenoid circuit.
Voltage of shift solenoid terminal is low although TCM is commanding shift solenoid to turn ON.
Voltage of shift solenoid terminal is high although TCM is commanding shift solenoid to turn OFF.

Internal Control Module Memory Check Sum Error
Calculation of current data stored in TCM is not correct comparing with pre-stored checking data in TCM.
Torque Request Communication Error from TCM
ECM detects abnormality of CAN communication data which TCM transmits.
4 position switch signal is inputted out of specified value.
Actual transfer position is 4H although transfer low signal is inputted.
Actual transfer position is 4L although transfer low signal is not inputted.
Variation in the output revolution speed of the specified amplitude and specified cycle is detected under slip look-up condition.
Torque Converter Clutch Pressure Control Solenoid Control Circuit Range / Performance

Torque Converter Clutch Pressure Control Solenoid Control Circuit High

Torque Converter Clutch Pressure Control Solenoid Control Circuit Low
No electric flow is detected on TCC pressure control solenoid circuit.
